pr_body:
# New: Task Room ## 1. Introduction This project was carried out as part of the Google Summer of Code'21. The objective was to create a new type of room in which users, instead of sending messages, could create tasks. The code has been built to accommodate future improvements. So for example some endpoints are not used, and some methdods are not used yet, but can easily become so with future features. In my opinion this project as it stands on 22-08-21 provides the basis for the task room, however there is still work to be done to make it operational for Rocket.chat users.

I am very motivated to continue this project after the GSOC as part of the Open-Source. [Presentation video](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cbh8nDvbTj0) Feedback of the mentor: ![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/45966964/137593195-a9a4986f-c681-4806-8b90-06c40f80cae6.png) ## 2. High level technical details #### 2.1. TaskRoom Rocket.Chat to render the rooms uses Meteor. However, here I used React. This choice was made because Rocket.Chat wants to move towards React for its new core functionality. A task room can be recognized in the DB because it has a taskRoomId property. This allows it to be Private or Public. The project also introduces new API endpoints. In addition, new permissions have been added. However, the permissions of the task room are lower than the permissions of the messages. For example, if a user does not have the right to send a message, but has the permission to create tasks, they cannot create a task. Notifications are active in the room. #### 2.2 Tasks inside the task room Moreover it is important to specify that a task is not a message behind the scene. Indeed a task has its own model in MongoDB and also its own front-end collection to use the fast-rendering feature. Moreover a task can become a thread header. So you can 'reply' to a task as if it were a thread. Thus, a task will take the UI of a thread header in the thread tab. So a task can have a tcount and a replies property. A task has 4 unique properties: Title, description, assignment, status. These 4 properties can be filled by the user to add content to the task. ## 3. High level features #### 3.1. TaskRoom 1. Thread Tab enabled 2. Can be C or P 3. Notifications 4. Allows you to manage tasks (CRUD) 5. Partial Optisitic UI #### 3.2. Tasks 1. You can update/create/delete a task 2. Reply to a task 3. Display the unread messages notifications of tasks header 4. Assign a title/assignees/status/description 5. Notifications & follow 6. Partial Optisitic UI 7. Message tcount ## 4. Work to be done - Improving the UI - Correcting edge cases bugs & bugs in general - Improving the 'loadmore' functionnality - Improving the Optimistic UI for some actions - Improving tests - Include a date/completed feature - Improving the assignment feature -> notification when your are the assignee ## 5. Acknowldgement Thanks to Pierre and Leonardo who took time out of their day to monitor me. I am very grateful to them. It was a rewarding experience to work with them. Thanks to Sing-Li and the Rocket.Chat community who organized the beginning of the GSOC period at RC.
If you have any questions about the code, please do not hesitate to contact me
